,Recommended,238750,8846882,"Posted: 25 January, 2014",all,Scote,"I've been reading some reviews on this game and they just seem silly to me, so I thought I might post one of my own.  First off, if you can't get past the Uplay don't even bother reading further.  I guess there is some issues if you have  32-bit OS as well...  I have a 64-bit OS so it isn't as issue for me.  You might want to check into that if do.Ok, so I fell in love with Might and Magic since I played M&M II: Gates to another world on the Sega Genesis.  I've played III, IV, V and VI all through completion.  I love the series!  I've also played Heroes of M&M I-VI.  THEY ARE DIFFERENT GAMES!  I saw reviews of people complaning this is nothing like Heroes...well...yeah!  It is nothing like Duel of Champions either!  The only thing this game has in common with Heroes is story background and creatures.  Game style is completely different!  I also saw a number of people comparing this to Grimlock.  Sounds like they were expecting this to be Grimlock but with an outside world.  I wonder if this is because all the Diablo Clones out there...Anyways...  Well, this games is completely different again.  Only thing in common with Grimlock is a party of 4 and a grid movement system.  Party make up and battles are different.  There is a lot more stratagy and party balance needed here.  You can't just take for rogues and expect to shoot/kite everything.  There is no kiting.  Mobs will catch you and eat you if you're not prepared.  You will learn what kind of attacks they have and will have to plan on what you need to do to counter them to keep your team alive.   It is turn based, so you know when to expect the attack.  Your four go, then the monsters go, repeat...  You will have time to think, because you'll need it.  This game does have a lot of do and explore.  I did play the early access and am a ways into act 1 of the full release.  Things have gotten much better than early access!  So don't read too much into reviews before 01/21/2014....  The music...I don't really care about music...I play games to play them not listen to music...  The game play is fun, complex and challenging so far.    If played other M&M games (again not Heroes) then you should like this.  If you like Grimlock and are open to more strategy in fighting and with less puzzles and kiting, then you'll probably like this...It this is a great game if you're not expecting it to be a clone of other games you've played...."
