76561198006647933,Not Recommended,238750,8856240,"Posted: 26 January, 2014",all,Low_K,"Might and Magic. Right. Not to be confused with the Heroes of Might and Magic series, which, went down the minute UbiSoft got the IP.This game has it flaws, actually many flaws. I'll note some cons of the game;- No front and rear positions- Your heroes are all in the front rank, and can be targeted by the enemies, so you cannot defend your magic users. There are a few spells which take some of the damage, but not having front and rear ranks is a bit of a oversight.- No means of retreating- Sometimes you make a mistake and aggro the wrong enemies, once you are locked into combat you cannot move away. So if you bite off more than you can chew; just load a previous save and save you the trouble of fighting a lost battle.- The graphics are really below par. Ofcourse graphics are not the most important things in these sort of games, but 2014 would mean at least some more eye-candy would be welcome. The graphics are bland, doors and NPCs made as if they are from the nineties. The day and night cycle is good though, but overall the graphics are not 2014 like,- The levelling up is way too much fuss. You'd think when you level up you can select abilities and skills on one screen. Not in this game; Here you need to edit your stats in the inventory screen, close it, open the spellbook and select more skill points for weapon/spells/etc. skills. Very annoying.- The customisation options- Really, 4 races with only 2 head options for females and males? Three classes per race is way too few. Customisation is very, very disappointing.- The Dialogues- Dialogues are very boring; If you expect anything like Mass Effect think again. Not much options to answer, usually only 2 and the dialogues really don't draw you into the story.- The graphics sometimes don't render and there are slow-downs at certain parts. Bad graphical optimisation.I can go on, but I think you get a general idea. Does this game have no plusses? Sure, but the cons really have the upper hand. Wait for a few more patches which hopefully will change a lot while the game feels very rushed.I think hardcore fans of the Might and Magic series could get some fun out of this game, but people like me, who like the Eye of the Beholder series and Wizardry 8, really don't need to buy this. It is overpriced and under-par. It tries to mimick the RPGs of old and fails.Shame really while it had potential to become a great game."
