76561197970588703,Not Recommended,238750,13979093,"Posted: 13 January, 2015",all,thrasher43,"The Might and Magic series has been one of my favorites for a long time... up until M&M9.  It was horrible.  I was very hopeful that M&M10 could restore the legacy and for the most part, it was a good step forward.  The tile-by-tile movement took awhile to get used to since everyone seems to use a ""free-look"" movement these days.  The very simplistic mapping system could use some help.  The graphics should have been much better given the amount of time that's passed since it's predecessor.  Combat could have been much less frustrating if the mobs had levels or some indication of how tough they were.  As it is, you don't know until the fight begins and your party is dead in two swings.  A lot of the quests were very vague, to the point where i had to Google about a dozen to figure out what I should be doing.  Lastly, I think the gameplay could be balanced a little better.  While I didn't play every possible party configuration, I think upwards of 60% of possible class combinations are doomed to fail.  The game should encourage you to mix it up rather than conform to the healer-warrior-ranged-magic combination and after three game restarts, that's how it felt to me."
