,Not Recommended,238750,8906000,"Posted: 29 January, 2014",all,krukid,"My first impression was that it has significantly more simplistic visuals than I'd expected, not very engaging gameplay and unremarkable game mechanics.Honestly, I just wanted a bigger Grimrock, which IMO was a masterpiece, in all of its humility. Not having played original M&M games I'd hoped there would be lots of lore to pick from and create a huge, immersive and rich environment. Sadly, the lore and opportunity may have been there, but the implementation went someplace else.Scale-wise it certainly is no Skyrim - a dozen of locations or so. To call it an ""open world"" is almost laughable with all the progression-based obstacles you coincidentally encounter at every turn - ranging from guards blocking a bridge and impassable terrain to hopeless fights. Talking about rich environment - there's not much role playing, aside from listening to gossips from NPCs with sporadic voice-overs, sifting through loot to find something that suits your party and wondering about the way you were supposed to distribute your skill points to not get brutalized all over the map after act one.In short: the dungeons are there, the quests are there, the loot is there, but it still feels like a farm sim - and not the best one."
