76561197981948882,Recommended,238750,9383233,"Posted: 8 March, 2014",all,eric,"Might & Magic X was a very positive surprise. The reviews were somewhat average, but I was looking for an old-style dungeon crawl and went ahead buying MMX shortly after it went out of early access. If you know what to expect (a tile and turned based game system), you might end up having a lot of fun with it.Graphics aren't the best, but look quite decent within dungeons (where you'll spent most of your time). I like the combat system, especially that you get the feeling of being in control and making good decisions without having to spent ages learning stats of weapons and spells. Almost 10 hours in, combat is still fun and I haven't encountered any frustrating difficulty spikes yet (although I faced some challenges).The story is rather weak, but then again, you're here for the dungeon crawl.I'm not a veteran MM player, but after MMX I'll definitely look into some of the classic parts of the series."
