76561198042975956,Recommended,238750,11612073,"Posted: 9 August, 2014",all,Nythauk,"M&M X: Legacy - for those of us who have been playing games BEFORE Steam, and before the internet was the monster it has become, there were games played on boards, and before that, paper. Once computers entered the gaming world a few people wrote games in text only format to entertain the infant market. I even wrote a Star Trek game on the Commodore 64 that was stored on a floppy disk! M&M X is a new game which captures a little of the older, but not as old as that old C64 game I wrote. And thank heaven for that! Greatly improved graphics over past iterations of the M&M world, smoother play, old style movement and enough creatures, bad guys, and other diversions to keep the most stout-hearted adventurer in the game for many hours. This game uses an older type of interface that the younger generation might find ""clunky"" but this is only because they have no basis for comparison. Humor is always required in an adventure game as are challenges which increase in difficulty level as progress is made make gaming as time consuming blast! The first dragon encountered is very much a challenge worthy of the best warrior party - for this dragon is beautiful but deadly. Cyclops are always a challenge and M&M X gets it right by inserting a cave with a cyclops standing inside the entrance and it carries a club. Your party is in grave danger and there is no leaving the cave until the danger is past...er...dead. Get a horse early and let it carry the extra armor and weapons you collect along the way, leaving your arms free to hold a sword and shiled. Keep gold in your pockets though, horses can't be trusted!Easy to play, addictive style that will captivate the most jaded players due to the strangely adaptive A.I., and graphics that are old-school and yet pleasing to the eye -- Might & Magic X: Legacy is a great game! Oh, yeah, and it comes with M&M VI, a definite blast-from-the-past title that will keep you journeying and adventuring for hours on end."
76561198025295885,Recommended,238750,11515075,"Posted: 1 August, 2014",all,JonasB,"Fun game, lots of variety in party builds, good old school RPG gameplay (even has a retro-pixel mode!) but without the confusing sheets of numbers--everything is laid out for you to see and nothing is really hidden.Good puzzles with clever variety, challenging fights especially with some of the bosses, and an intriguing story as well. Having said this, the game does suffer from a lack of polish in terms of graphics and animations. It also uses Uplay which some people hate with a vengeance but I haven't had any problems with. But if you like Grimrock, baldur's gate, wizardry, or the older Might and Magic games (even 6, despite the lack of real-time mode in X), you'll find MMX quite satisfying."
