76561198042318117,Recommended,238750,21837282,"Posted: 14 March, 2016",all,Zammy,"I got this game as a part of a bundle and thought ""well, this will be one game I'll nevel install"".But I ended up trying the game, and liked it so much I completed it.Despite being released in 2014, Might and Magic X has a very strong back to 90' feeling looming over it. It mostly feels like a weird mixture of roguelike and older Might and Magic games. Turn based game where you run in a grid. Certainly not something you would expect from such a new game.I, however, find this pleasant and nostalgic.If you like older Might and Magic titles and are fan of roguelikes, then this game will be good for you, try it out if it's on sale.If you aren't fan of either, better stay away. You will probably not like this.There are two major downsides for this game I disliked.-Damn much running around in same places.-No real game notes. Too often you keep wondering ""where on earth I saw that earth magic master teacher. Gotta go to google again, I'm not checking the whole world again to find him.""They certainly didn't stop me from playing, but I must admid both were annoying for me."
