,Recommended,238750,14348890,"Posted: 5 February, 2015",all,Blast X Blast,"I like the game, but it's not for everyone. Here's a tip for anyone that has trouble getting the game to remember your saves:Find the folder with the U-Play exe, right click and set to run as administrator. Go to the main game folder (mine is programfilesx86/Steam/SteamApps/Common/MMX) and right click the exe and also set to run as admin.For some reason the game requires admin privilege to make any changes whatsoever to a folder...even recording a save.As for the game itself, it's basically like crossing Might and Magic III with Might and Magic VI...and then stripping it of virtually all depth in exchange for accessibility. I like the game...because I like the M&M universe and other games in the series (including the excellent Heroes games). But, like the Heroes games, it's weak sauce compared to the earlier entries. Judging it by Might and Magic standards, I give it a 5 out of 10...if that. But by gaming standards...it's not bad IMO. Maybe 7 out of 10....maybe too generous. I like it, but it's not for everyone.While I recommend the game, I have to recommend you first watch some let's plays and get a feel for what the game entails before purchasing. It's NOT anything like Legend of Grimrock (which is what led a lot of people astray into purchasing the game...LoG and it's sequel are objectively better and vastly different). Also keep in mind the game is no longer supported by Ubisoft and the forums are dead...so you're on your own for the most part.In short, I enjoy the game...but it's certainly a small niche type of game. Chances are, it's not for you. Buyer beware."
